==English==

=== Pronunciation ===
'''Ap-proxi-mate-ly'''
AHD phonetic symbols: [ă-prŏksə-mĭt-lē]


=== Adverb ===
'''approximately''' (abbreviated as ''approx.'' or ''e'')
# [[imprecise]] but close to in [[quantity]] or [[amount]]


====Translations====
Portuguese: [[aproximadamente]]
*Telugu: [[సుమారుగా]] (sumaarugaa)

===Synonyms===
* [[around]], [[near]], [[nearly]], [[almost]], [[about]], [[loosely]], [[roughly]], close to
===Antonyms===
* [[accurately]], [[definitely]], [[exactly]], [[precisely]]
=== Related terms ===
*[[approximate]]

=== Examples ===
*In every box of matches there is ''approximately'' 40 matchsticks.
*Per 100g of chocolate there is ''approximately'' 11.6g of saturated fat.
*Each packet of potato chips contains 35g '''e'''
*Musical quotation ''approximately 60 beats per minute''

=== Quotations ===

<blockquote>
"''A small core of the wood is removed and the rings are painstakingly counted. This remarkable tree was '''approximately''' 1400 years old''"
</blockquote> waynesworld.palomar.edu [http://waynesword.palomar.edu/treedate.htm]

<blockquote>
"''I cut out meat '''approximately''' 10 years ago and dairy about 5 years ago''"
</blockquote> Peter Brock

